          "verseNum": 3,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 4,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "For the Lord has chosen Jacob for himself, Israel as his own possession. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 4,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "For the Lord has chosen Jacob for himself, Israel as his own possession."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 4,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 5,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "For I know that the Lord is great, and that our Lord is above all gods. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 5,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "For I know that the Lord is great, and that our Lord is above all gods."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 5,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 6,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Whatever the Lord pleases, he does, in heaven and on earth, in the seas and all deeps. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 6,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "Whatever the Lord pleases, he does, in heaven and on earth, in the seas and all deeps."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 6,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "Whatever the Lord pleases, he does, in heaven and on earth, in the seas and all deeps."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 6,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 7,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "He it is who makes the clouds rise at the end of the earth, who makes lightnings for the rain and brings forth the wind from his storehouses. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 7,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "He it is who makes the clouds rise at the end of the earth, who makes lightnings for the rain and brings forth the wind from his storehouses."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 7,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "He it is who makes the clouds rise at the end of the earth, who makes lightnings for the rain and brings forth the wind from his storehouses."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 7,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 8,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "He it was who struck down the firstborn of Egypt, both of man and of beast; "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 8,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "He it was who struck down the firstborn of Egypt, both of man and of beast;"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 8,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 9,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "who in your midst, O Egypt, sent signs and wonders against Pharaoh and all his servants; "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 9,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "who in your midst, O Egypt, sent signs and wonders against Pharaoh and all his servants;"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 9,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 10,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "who struck down many nations and killed mighty kings, "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 10,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "who struck down many nations and killed mighty kings,"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 10,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 11,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Sihon, king of the Amorites, and Og, king of Bashan, and all the kingdoms of Canaan, "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 11,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "Sihon, king of the Amorites, and Og, king of Bashan, and all the kingdoms of Canaan,"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 11,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 12,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "and gave their land as a heritage, a heritage to his people Israel. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 12,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 13,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Your name, O Lord, endures forever, your renown, O Lord, throughout all ages. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 13,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "Your name, O Lord, endures forever, your renown, O Lord, throughout all ages."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 13,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 14,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "For the Lord will vindicate his people and have compassion on his servants. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 14,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "For the Lord will vindicate his people and have compassion on his servants."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 14,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 15,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "The idols of the nations are silver and gold, the work of human hands. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 15,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "The idols of the nations are silver and gold, the work of human hands."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 15,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 16,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "They have mouths, but do not speak; they have eyes, but do not see; "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 16,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "They have mouths, but do not speak; they have eyes, but do not see;"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 16,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 17,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "they have ears, but do not hear, nor is there any breath in their mouths. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 17,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "they have ears, but do not hear, nor is there any breath in their mouths."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 17,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": " "
        },
        {
          "verseNum": 18,
          "hasVerseLabel": true,
          "verseText": "Those who make them become like them, so do all who trust in them. "
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "line-quote",
      "contents": [
        {
          "verseNum": 18,
          "hasVerseLabel": false,
          "verseText": "Those who make them become like them, so do all who trust in them."
